A young motocross rider stands next to the course at Gotham Mountain in upstate New York. A little late posting this, but great to have been a part of the Eddie Adams XXXII Workshop this year. Would definitely recommend it to photographers!  #eddieadams #eaw2019 #motocross

Up until now I’ve only ever posted my own work on this feed, but couldn’t pass up showing off this fantastic piece of art I was lucky enough to acquire from one of my favorite Kenyan artists, the very talented #wycliffeopondo aka #wiki. Makes me laugh every time! #kenya #nairobi #photostudio #kuonatrust
A Dinka tribesman sings to his cattle as the sun sets over his cattle camp next to the Nile river in the Jonglei state of South Sudan. #southsudan #nile #cattlecamp

Roshni, an Azuree 46, sits at anchor underneath the Pitons in St. Lucia after a 16 day sail across the Atlantic that began in the Canary Islands off the coast of Morocco. Not a bad way to end the trip! #sailinglife #stlucia
A young child sits underneath some plants on his family’s farm next to the #nile river in the town of Bor in South Sudan. #southsudanese #southsudan
A South Sudanese woman waters her vegetable garden using water from the nearby #nile river in the town of Bor in #southsudan. #farmhousekitchen
Young men push bicycles loaded with cassava up a hill on their way to the local market in the Ruhango district of Rwanda. #rwanda #cassava #bicycles
Mist covers the valley floor as the morning light filters through the clouds in the Makamba province of Burundi. #burundi #mist #dronenature
Antoine, an elderly farmer who’s been growing cassava his whole life, helps to fill a sack during harvest season on his farm in the Ruhango district of Rwanda. #rwanda #farmer #cassava
The sun sets over the Rwandan hills, dotted with farmhouses, in the Ruhango district of the country. #rwanda #visitrwanda #farmhouse

A young Shona girl wears one of the baskets her family weaves as a hat, while at home in Nairobi, Kenya. The Shona community in #kenya are a #stateless community, having come over in the 1970’s from Zimbabwe, and now have neither Kenyan or Zimbabwean citizenship. #unhcrkenya #unhcr

A young girl waits to have her blood checked as part of Access Afya’s healthy schools program in #nairobi, #kenya. Access Afya are a chain of low cost clinics catering to some of Nairobi’s poorest communities in the country’s capital. #healthcare #clinic #schoolgirl #accessafya
Early morning sun lights up the plains over the savanna in Suswa, Kenya. #savanna #kenya #landscape_lover

A young boy, holding a bundle of dried reeds, waits for them to be set on fire before transferring them to his father’s funeral pyre at a crematorium on the banks of the Ganges River in the city of Varanasi, India. #india #varanasi #death #hinduism #gangesriver

A young man holds his brothers hand while they take turns to bathe in the Ganges River, before cremating their father at one of the river’s holiest sites nearby. #India #ganges #varanasi #LI #hinduism #hindu
A worker tends to a fire at a crematorium on the banks of the Ganges in the Indian city of #varanasi. #LI #ganges #india

A snake charmer sits with his young child and two cobras outside of the tent where they live near the city of #varanasi in #india. Although snake charming has been illegal in India since 1991, the tradition is more than 2000 years old and a way of life that has been passed down from generation to generation amongst certain groups. #snakes #LI #cobra
A portrait of one of India’s sadhus along the Ganges River in the Indian city of Varanasi. #varanasi #india #LI

A bird flys by the ruins of Mogadishu’s old cathedral in Somalia’s capitol. The cathedral was built by the Italian colonial authorities in 1928 and was the biggest in Eastern Africa at the time. It was destroyed in 2008 by Islamic radicals. #somalia #LI #cathedral #mogadishu
An old road cuts through a forest on New Zealand’s South Island near the town of Franz Josef. #newzealand #franzjosef

Breakfast aboard the 48ft Roshni during her 2800 mile transatlantic voyage across the Atlantic from the Canary Islands to St. Lucia in the Caribbean. The route, known as the “Milk Run”, involves sailing south towards Cape Verde to escape the doldrums and then West to use the trade winds to get to the Caribbean. #caribbean #sailing #transatlantic

Untitled #8. Demographica is an ongoing project that blends photography and demography to create a typology of 100 portraits that does its best to statistically represent the makeup of a country’s population. The aim of Demographica is to paint a true representation of a country, dispelling the various misconceptions and stereotypes people may have, and revealing the actual diversity of the many different people who make up any one population. #demographica #demographics #population #kenya
